gmd:abstract.gco:CharacterString: University and College Areas. The dataset contains locations and attributes of University AreasC. Office of the Chief Technology Officer (OCTO) and participating D.C. government agencies. Information provided by OCTO This layer does not represent university areas contained in the campus plans from the DC Office of Zoning. All DC GIS data is stored and exported in Maryland State Plane coordinates NAD 83 meters. METADATA CONTENT IS IN PROCESS OF VALIDATION AND SUBJECT TO CHANGE.

gmd:description.gco:CharacterString: Added Augustinian and Theological Colleges after performing regular maintenance on layer.

gmd:organisationName.gco:CharacterString: Office of the Chief Technology Officer

gmd:description.gco:CharacterString: * Extended length of NAME fied to 75 from 50 (for UniversPt) * Reviewed Names of Schools (spellling etc) * Standardized name to 'George Washington University at Mount Vernon College' (both Pt and Ply) * Made sure number of records in UniversPt = UnivesityPly * Updated GWU & Georgetown polygons * Added 16 Universities and colleges there were minor ones.

Universities were identified from public records and university websites. They were snapped to select snapbase features and heads-up digitized from the 2003 orthophotographs to create complete campus boundaries. In most cases, these boundaries were captured using the ADC maps. Staff inferred boundaries from campus maps to close the boundaries.

gmd:organisationName.gco:CharacterString: Office of the Chief Technology Officer

gmd:description.gco:CharacterString: Staff reviewed the campus areas abd redefined them based on the vector property map. Before, there were residential areas contained in colleges in error. The new boundaries are more representative of the actual university ownership coverage.

gmd:maintenanceNote.gco:CharacterString: Metadata was created as or translated to ISO 19139 for inclusion in the Big Ten Academic Alliance Geoportal.
